title: Food Access Research Atlas
description: The Food Access Research Atlas presents an overview of food access indicators for low-income and other census tracts using different measures of supermarket accessibility. It provides food access data for populations within census tracts and it offers census-tract-level data on food access that can be downloaded for community planning or research purposes.
creator: Economic Research Service (ERS), U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA)
subject: Food Environment
methods_variables: Urban tracts; Group quarters, tract with a high share; Tracts with low vehicle access; Flags for low-income and low-access tracts using 1 mile and 10 miles thresholds; Flags for low-access tracts using 20-mile thresholds in rural areas.
data_variables: Housing units, total; Population with low access at 1 mile for urban areas and 10 miles for rural areas; Population with low access at 1/2 mile for urban areas and 10 miles for rural areas; Population with low access at 1 mile for urban areas and 20 miles for rural areas; Low-income population with low access at 1 mile for urban areas and 10 miles for rural areas; Low-income population with low access at 1/2 mile for urban areas and 10 miles for rural areas; Low-income population with low access at 1 mile for urban areas and 20 miles for rural areas; Population with low access at 1/2 mile; Population share with low access at 1/2 mile; Low-income population with low access at 1/2 mile; Share of low-income population with low access at 1/2 mile; Children (age 0-17) with low access at 1/2 mile; Share of children (age 0-17) with low access at 1/2 mile; Seniors (age 65+) with low access at 1/2 mile; Share of seniors (age 65+) with low access at 1/2 mile; White population with low access at 1/2 mile; Share of White population with low access at 1/2 mile; Black or African American population with low access at 1/2 mile; Share of Black or African American population with low access at 1/2 mile; Hispanic or Latino population with low access at 1 mile; Share of Hispanic or Latino population with low access at 1 mile; Housing units receiving SNAP benefits and with low access at 10 miles; Share of housing units receiving SNAP benefits and with low access at 10 miles.
featured_variable: Low-income and low-access tracts at 1 mile for urban areas and 10 miles for rural areas; Low-income and low-access tracts at 1/2 mile for urban areas and 10 miles for rural areas; Low-income and low-access tracts at 1 mile for urban areas and 20 miles for rural areas; Tracts with low vehicle access and low income at 20 miles in rural areas.
preferred_citation: Economic Research Service (ERS), U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA). Food Access Research Atlas, https://www.ers.usda.gov/data-products/food-access-research-atlas/
data_usage_notes: Estimates in the Atlas for 2019 are based on a 2019 list of supermarkets, the 2010 Decennial Census, and the 2014-18 American Community Survey (ACS). The estimates for 2015 are based on a 2015 list of supermarkets, the 2010 Decennial Census, and the 2010-14 ACS.
